<subSubSection box="[151,519,223,249]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,223,394]" box="[151,519,223,249]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,519,223,249]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,519,223,249]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1905" box="[207,341,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Apechoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricornis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,341,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">nigricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="202" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,223,394]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Gauld, I. D." box="[310,466,259,285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" pagination="1 - 453" refId="ref5550" refString="Gauld, I. D. (2000) The Ichneumonidae of Costa Rica 3. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 63, 1 - 453. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2000. tb 00015. x" type="journal article" year="2000">Gauld (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, this group is characterised by the female not possessing an indentation on the hind margin of tergite VII (
<figureCitation box="[405,561,295,322]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–60" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,181,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-21@14.[151,1436,181,1910]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 53–60. A. pictiventris (female specimen from Peru). 53 &amp; 55–60 Photographs. 53 Hind wings, 54 Hind wing (Drawing), 55 Mesosoma (dorsal view), 56 Metasoma (lateral view), 57 Metasoma (dorsal view), 58 Ovipositor, 59 Metasoma (apical part, lateral view), 60 Metasoma (apical part, dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810077/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Figs 57 &amp; 60</figureCitation>
), and by the absence of epicnemial carina in both female and male (
<figureCitation box="[1343,1431,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–27" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[198,1392,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@7.[195,1392,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22–27. Photographs of A. nigriventris (female specimen from Peru). 22 Habitus (lateral view), 23 Metasoma (apical part), 24 Head (frontal view), 25 Propodeum (dorsolateral view), 26 Head, mesosoma &amp; tergite I (lateral view), 27 Head &amp; anterior part of mesosoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810061/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">Figs 26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,181,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–32" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1730,1754]" captionTargetBox="[152,1427,184,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[151,1436,181,1706]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28–32. A. nigriventris. 28 Fore wing (drawing) (female specimen from Peru). 29–32 (male specimen from Peru). 29 &amp; 30 Photographs, 31 &amp; 32 Drawings. 29 Habitus (lateral view), 30 Metasoma (apical part), 31 Fore wing, 32 Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810063/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">29</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[196,268,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURES 61–73" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1621,1645]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,181,1597]" captionTargetId="figure-20@15.[151,1436,181,1598]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 61–73. A. nigriventris (male specimen from Peru). 61–69, 71 &amp; 73 Photographs, 70 &amp; 72 Drawings. 61 Habitus (lateral view), 62 Habitus (dorsal view), 63 Head (dorsal view), 64 Head &amp; anterior part of mesosoma (lateral view), 65 Mesosoma (lateral view), 66 Mesosoma (dorsal view), 67 Metasoma (apical part, dorsal view), 68 Hind wing, 69 Wings, 70 Fore wing, 71 Metasoma (lateral view), 72 Hind wing, 73 Metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810079" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810079/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">64, 65</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[309,341,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 74–80" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,185,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-21@16.[151,1436,181,1906]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 74–80. Holotype of A. seminigra Flórez, 2012 (female). 74–78 Photographs, 79 &amp; 80 Drawings. 74 Habitus (lateral view), 75 Habitus (dorsal view), 76 Head, mesosoma &amp; tergite I (lateral view), 77 Mesosoma (dorsal view), 78 Wings, 79 Fore wing, 80 Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810081" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810081/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">76</figureCitation>
). Only one species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1905" box="[579,737,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Apechoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricornis">
<emphasis box="[579,737,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">A. nigricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) was considered in this group by Gauld; now we include 
<taxonomicName authority="Mocsary, 1905" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Apechoneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="202">A. nigriventris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mocsary, A." box="[289,455,367,394]" pageId="1" pageNumber="202" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref5645" refString="Mocsary, A. (1905) Rhyssae sociarumque species in collection Musei Nationalis Hungarici. Annales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 3, 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="1905">Mocsáry, 1905</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
within this group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
